Class SignatureElement

java.lang.Object
  |
  +--edu.caltech.sbw.SignatureElement
public class SignatureElement
extends java.lang.Object

A signature element in SBW is a name-type pair in a method signature, with the name portion being optional. This provides a single common structure for representing both method arguments (where an argument may be either a data type or a data type followed by a name) and method return types. For example, the method signature "void foo(string a, int b" contains two signature elements in its argument list, string a and int b, and one signature element for the return type, void.

equals

public final boolean equals(SignatureElement se)
The standard equals method of the Java Object class is overloaded to permit comparison between two SignatureElement objects. The equality is determined on the basis of the signature data types only, not the name portion.

Parameters:
se - a SignatureElement object to compare this one to
Returns:
